THE Ekiti State Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, Bisi Kolawole, on Tuesday, promised to run an issue-based campaign as it prepares for the 2022 Governorship Election. Kolawole, who is also one of the party’s aspirants for the election, made the promise while inaugurating his 200-member campaign committee headed by a former House of Representatives member, Segun Adekola. This was contained in a statement titled, ‘Ekiti 2022: Ex-Rep member to lead Bisi Kolawole’s campaign, over 200-member campaign committee constituted’, signed by the Director of Media and Publicity of the campaign organisation, Lere Olayinka. Olayinka announced plans by the campaign to commence a local government tour of all 16 Local Government Areas of the State, on Sunday. He said the event will be flagged off in Efon-Alaaye. The statement further noted that other members of the committee billed to be inaugurated next week, include: former PDP Deputy Governorship candidate, Deji Ogunsakin (Director of Administration and Strategy), and former members of House of Representatives, Kehinde Agboola, Thaddeus Aina and Ayo Oladimeji among others. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com